You can use the colinear component of your player velocity as your velocity upon entering the curve. From there the curve is only providing direction and the velocity along the curve can be calculated as some combination of gravity and the player's velocity projected onto the spline normal wherever the player is. When I glance at the godot docs it seems like you can get the point on the curve nearest the player which serves as your entry point.
